commit.message:
Fix possible bar redraw delay

Redraw bar on 'ws_next_move'/'ws_prev_move'.

Redraw bar when switching to an empty region.

Fixes #555

Fix `swap_main` window list insert issue

Fixes #557

Improve RandR checks

Fix building against XCB with RandR < 1.6.

Remove unused RROutputChangeNotify event selection on bar window(s).

Remove Xlib RandR include since its version macros are no longer used.

Note that region detection requires RandR >= 1.3 since spectrwm 1.1.2.

Closes #554

Fix bar color issues

Fix handling of normal/unfocus/free bar colors with different counts.

Fix bar colors should be per X screen.

Add missing 'bar_font_color_free' entry to man page.

Add notes to man page about color index limits and fallback behavior.

Resolves #548

README: Some tweaks

Mostly get rid of trailing whitespace.

CHANGELOG: Some tweaks

Mostly make symbols (e.g. _NET_WM_NAME) use monospace font.

This looks better when rendered as HTML by GitHub, and also
it doesn't confuse syntax highlighting for editors such as
vim quite as much.

I've limited the changes to the most recent few entries,
because those are the ones that are already using Markdown
syntax extensively, which means that just a few small tweaks
were needed instead of much more invasive changes.

Fix typo in debug message

Spotted by Lintian.
Fix EWMH `_NET_WM_DESKTOP` requests should not bypass `workspace_limit`

Fix listing of empty workspaces in `bar_format` `+U` and `+L`

Fixes #547

Fix escape handling of `+` in `bar_action` script output

Fix limit/padding in 'bar_format' sequences where '+' is auto-escaped.

Fixes #546
Release spectrwm 3.5.1

Fix iconified windows should uniconify on MapRequest.

For example, when iconifying a window by clicking a button in an
application's UI, uniconify the window if the application tries to map
it again.

Fix focus fallback when iconifying windows via ClientMessage requests.

Fix focus fallback on iconify should be the same as closing windows.
Improve handling of client positioning of windows.
Fix urgency hint `+U` workspaces should start at 1.

Add SWMHACK section to man page.

Add examples to man page on how to override the spawn workspace.

Update list of default quirks in man page.

Closes #525
Fix `autorun` should accept `ws[-1]` as stated in the manual.

Fix `bar_color_free` and `bar_font_color_free` options.

Fixes #539

Fix typo in man page.

Update html manual.

Fixes #538
Fix `WS[-1]` should put a window into free mode as stated in the manual.
Allow manually building with XCB XInput via `-DSWM_XCB_HAS_XINPUT`.

Fix NetBSD build issues.

Add NetBSD to XCB X Input 2 support whitelist.

Wrap string to integer conversion and use strtoi() on NetBSD.

Fix build failure when building without X Input 2 support.

Fix compiler warnings on NetBSD.

Fix get_swm_ws() return value on failure.
Fix segfault at startup when managing a mapped window under the pointer.
Fix maximize new windows in max layout when `max_layout_maximize = 1`.

Fix `bar_at_bottom` bottom gap when `bar_border_width` > 0.

Fix typo in changelog.
Update changelog and release spectrwm 3.5.0!

Address usability issue of _NET_WM_MOVERESIZE on tiled/maximized windows.

Add new 'snapping' behavior to tiled/maximized windows.
Prevents inadvertantly floating tiled/maximized windows with the
pointer. Needed to avoid immediately untiling windows that initiate a
move operation when clicked, such as some video players, browsers, etc.

Add new `snap_range` option (default: 25).
Set the distance in pixels a tiled/maximized window must be moved (with
the pointer) to unsnap and float freely. Set to 0 to float immediately
when a move operation begins.

Add size direction macros and keep EWMH moveresize conversion separate.

Add support for _NET_WM_MOVERESIZE.

Enables applications to initiate a move/resize operation via EWMH.
For example, some application windows have areas that can be clicked to
move/resize the window.

Add 'cancelkey' option (default: Escape).
Change the key used as an alternative means of terminating move/resize.

Update html manual.
Fix rg_move_next/rg_move_prev should ignore workspace_clamp.

Fix zero border_width/bar_border_width

A zero line width on Xcb is handled as a "thin line", which is usually
at least one pixel. Do not draw the window or bar frame when the border
is explicitly set to zero.
